🏥 Real-Time Healthcare Data Engineering Pipeline on GCP

Build a Real-Time Healthcare Data Engineering Project on Google Cloud Platform (GCP).

This project implements a Patient Vitals Monitoring System — an end-to-end streaming data pipeline that runs entirely in the cloud and processes healthcare data in real time.

The system streams patient vitals such as heart rate, oxygen saturation (SpO₂), and body temperature using Google Cloud Pub/Sub, processes the streaming data using Apache Beam on Dataflow, and stores analytics-ready data in BigQuery following the Medallion Architecture (Bronze → Silver → Gold).

Finally, the processed data is visualized in Power BI dashboards, enabling real-time monitoring of patient health metrics.

This architecture reflects how modern healthcare platforms process IoT-style medical data streams for real-time analytics and decision-making.

📊 Project Architecture
Patient Simulator (Python)
        │
        ▼
   Google Cloud Pub/Sub
        │
        ▼
   Dataflow (Apache Beam)
        │
        ├─────────────► Bronze Layer (Raw Data - GCS)
        │
        ▼
   Silver Layer (Cleaned Data - GCS)
        │
        ▼
   Gold Layer (Analytics Data - BigQuery)
        │
        ▼
   Power BI Dashboard

Pipeline Flow

A Python simulator generates patient vitals.

Data is streamed into Pub/Sub topics.

Dataflow streaming pipelines process incoming data.

Data is stored using the Medallion Architecture.

Analytics data is visualized in Power BI dashboards.

🥇 Medallion Architecture

The project uses a multi-layer Medallion Architecture to structure and improve data quality through different processing stages. The architecture organizes data into Bronze, Silver, and Gold layers, where each layer represents a higher level of data refinement and usability.

Bronze Layer (Raw Data)

Stores raw streaming data directly from Pub/Sub

Data is stored in Google Cloud Storage (GCS)

No transformations applied

Silver Layer (Cleaned Data)

Data cleaning and transformation

Handles schema normalization

Removes invalid or duplicate records

Gold Layer (Analytics Layer)

Aggregated and business-ready datasets

Stored in BigQuery

Used for analytics, dashboards, and reporting

This layered architecture improves data governance, scalability, and analytics readiness.

⚙️ Technologies Used
Technology	Purpose
Google Cloud Platform	Cloud infrastructure
Pub/Sub	Real-time streaming data ingestion
Dataflow (Apache Beam)	Stream processing and ETL
Google Cloud Storage	Bronze & Silver data layers
BigQuery	Analytics data warehouse
Power BI	Data visualization dashboards
Python	Simulator and pipeline development
Git & GitHub	Version control

Google Cloud Pub/Sub enables event-driven streaming architectures, allowing systems to process data in real time across distributed services.
Dataflow provides a fully managed platform for scalable batch and streaming data processing using Apache Beam.

